<accessionNumber isEnumeration="true">BBH 22744, BCC 28581</accessionNumber>
), MY2771 (
<accessionNumber isEnumeration="true">BBH 22745, BCC 28582</accessionNumber>
), MY2775 (
<accessionNumber isEnumeration="true">BBH 22747, BBC 28585</accessionNumber>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia novoguineensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="novoguineensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia novoguineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. nelumboides" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nelumboides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. nelumboides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both species producing fertile heads at the terminal end of stipes. The perithecia are completely immersed. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. novoguineensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novoguineensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. novoguineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. nelumboides" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nelumboides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. nelumboides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in producing whole ascospores. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, IMA Fungus 8: 349" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Kobayasi &amp; Shimizu" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia nelumboides" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="nelumboides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia nelumboides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
produces multiseptated ascospores disarticulating into part-spores (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4119402" author="Kobayasi, Y" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="557 - 566" refId="B22" refString="Kobayasi, Y, Shimizu, D, 1977. Some species of Cordyceps and its allies on spiders. Kew Bulletin 31 (3): 557 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4119402" title="Some species of Cordyceps and its allies on spiders." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4119402" volume="31" year="1977">Kobayasi and Shimizu 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shimizu, D" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" refId="B48" refString="Shimizu, D, 1994. Color iconography of vegetable wasps and plant worms (in Japanese). Seibundo Shinkosha, Tokyo." title="Color iconography of vegetable wasps and plant worms (in Japanese). Seibundo Shinkosha, Tokyo." year="1994">Shimizu 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Based on natural specimens, the conidia from Thai specimens are shorter than those reported for specimens from Papua New Guinea (2-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
vs. 10.5-17.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(82)80065-X" author="Samson, RA" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the British Mycological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="571 - 572" refId="B44" refString="Samson, RA, Brady, BL, 1982. Akanthomyces novoguineensis sp. nov. Transactions of the British Mycological Society 79 (3): 571 - 572, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(82)80065-X" title="Akanthomyces novoguineensis sp. nov." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(82)80065-X" volume="79" year="1982">Samson and Brady 1982</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, there are other species producing the fertile heads at the terminal end of stipes infecting ants (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, in Kepler, Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones, Quandt, Sung, Rehner, Aime, Henkel, Sanjuan, Zare, Chen, Li, Rossman, Spatafora, Shrestha, IMA Fungus 8: 348" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
), for example, 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Ophiocordyceps" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ophiocordyceps binata" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="binata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Ophiocordyceps binata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(H.C. Evans &amp; Samson) J.P.M. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Araújo">Araujo</normalizedToken>
, H.C. Evans &amp; D.P. Hughes, 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. pseudolloydii" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="pseudolloydii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">O. pseudolloydii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(H.C. Evans &amp; Samson) G.H. Sung, J.M. Sung, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora and 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. lloydii" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="lloydii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">O. lloydii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(H.S. Fawc.) G.H. Sung, J.M. Sung, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2020.1822093" author="Araujo, JPM" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="1138 - 1170" refId="B2" refString="Araujo, JPM, Evans, HC, Fernandes, IO, Ishler, MJ, Hughes, DP, 2020. Zombie-ant fungi cross continents: II. Myrmecophilous hymenostilboid species and a novel zombie lineage. Mycologia 112 (6): 1138 - 1170, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2020.1822093" title="Zombie-ant fungi cross continents: II. Myrmecophilous hymenostilboid species and a novel zombie lineage." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2020.1822093" volume="112" year="2020">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Araújo">Araujo</normalizedToken>
et al. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Ophiocordyceps" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ophiocordyceps binata" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="binata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Ophiocordyceps binata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. novoguineensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novoguineensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. novoguineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by producing disc-shaped fertile heads, while fertile heads in 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. pseudolloydii" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="pseudolloydii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">O. pseudolloydii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. lloydii" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="lloydii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">O. lloydii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are subglobose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
